With this Git repository, the simulations and Figures 2 and 3 can be reproduced.  
Please note that the analyses in the paper were performed using a high-throughput batch system.  
The system used consists of 11 nodes with 96 GB to 768 GB memory and 12 to 64 CPUs.  

This repository implements the same calculations on a local system, which may result in long computation times.  

To simulate the results and generate the plots, please follow these steps:
1) Open the R project "simulation.Rproj".  
2) Run the script "01run_simulations.R" to simulate the data. Details are provided in the script header.  
   With the default settings, the runtime is approximately 5 to 10 minutes on a standard local computer.  
   You may choose a higher number of repetitions and simulated settings, but this will increase the runtime.  
3) Open the script "02figure2.R" and/or "02figure3.R" to generate the plots based on the simulated data from step 2.  

If you want to use the original simulated data from the paper, please download the data from Zenodo (https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19467860), unpack it, and store it in the "data" folder.  
In both scripts ("02figure2.R" and "02figure3.R"), the corresponding lines for using this data are already included but commented out.  
Please uncomment these lines and comment out the lines that use the simulated data from the steps above.  

